        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sought",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Rather, were seeking. The word involves a continuous effort, and probably includes the memorable meeting in the Palace of Caiaphas, which is traditionally placed on the ‘Hill of Evil Counsel,’ but was probably close to the Temple precincts. They seem to have come on that occasion, in consequence of the advice of Caiaphas, to three conclusions. (1) To put Jesus to death; (2) to do it as secretly as possible; and (3) not to do it during the Feast, so as to avoid the chance of tumults on the part of the Galilaean pilgrims. If this meeting was on Tuesday evening, at the very time that they were deciding ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "not",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to kill Jesus (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 2:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") for more than eight days—and it was unusual to put to death during the Passover, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 12:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—He, seated on the slopes of Olivet, was telling His disciples that before the Passover He should be slain, ",
